{"bill":{"bill_id":1639435,"change_hash":"17d45b09bec6c93018824e8002cfd097","session_id":2020,"session":{"session_id":2020,"state_id":13,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2024,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023-2024 Regular Session","session_name":"103rd General Assembly"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IL\/bill\/HB1015\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/www.ilga.gov\/legislation\/BillStatus.asp?DocNum=1015&GAID=17&DocTypeID=HB&SessionID=112&GA=103","completed":0,"status":1,"status_date":"2023-01-12","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-12","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-12","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-21","event":9}],"state":"IL","state_id":13,"bill_number":"HB1015","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":35,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":35,"title":"CRT CLAIMS-UNJUST IMPRISONMENT","description":"Amends the Court of Claims Act. Deletes language regarding the amount a court shall award to a person for time unjustly served in prison when the person imprisoned received a pardon on the ground of innocence of the crime for which he or she was imprisoned or he or she received a certificate of innocence. Provides instead that the court shall award $50,000 per year during which the person was wrongfully imprisoned and shall prorate that amount for a fraction of a year that the person was wrongfully imprisoned, including the number of years the person was awaiting trial. Provides that the court shall award attorney's fees in an amount not to exceed 25% of the award granted. Provides that the changes made by the amendatory Act apply to all claims pending or filed on or after the effective date. Effective immediately.","pending_committee_id":3302,"committee":{"committee_id":3302,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":35,"name":"Judiciary - Criminal"},"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-12","committee_id":235,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":35,"name":"Rules"},{"date":"2023-02-21","committee_id":3302,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":35,"na